text: I know everybody over reacts in sports these days - but how on earth does Michigan not fire Brady Hocke?   He deserved to be fired anyway for the car fire of a program he is running right now (the first time ever in the history of history that michigan has lost 3 games before October) - but you watch hole 4th quarter...  seeing Morris barely able to stand becuas of whatever leg injury he suffered...  continuing to get sacked...  and he's only 7/18 for 49 yards and you still leave him in...  even then after he gets nailed in the head...

after you finally replace him, putting first sting guy back in who gets hurt, you put Morris back in the game? The third string guy was headed out onto the field and the coach called him off the field to put the severely injured (both leg and head) back into the game...  absolutely insane.  Morris finally left the field on cart.
this clip shows a bunch of it.
